main event: A reddish-brown object approximately 15-30 feet in size was observed traveling north at high speed in March 1957.
interesting points: The sighting lasted for less than 1 minute but was documented over a 5-day observation period.,The object was reported to be at an altitude of 2000 feet.,The witness was considered reliable, and the investigator deemed the information source trustworthy.,The observation was classified as visual (D) with supporting documentation provided.,The document was from the Project Blue Book files, part of a US Air Force UFO investigation program.
location: 10 Mi NE of Blaisdell, N.D., USA
